Problem in HP-UX with +DA2.0W
-----------------------------

+DA2.0W results in sizeof(long) == 8
Numeric lapack_lite_module uses the long type for Fortran integer arguments
/usr/lib/pa20_64/lapack.sl has 4 byte integer arguments

Possible resolution I:
  Do not use /usr/lib/pa20_64/lapack.sl
  compile all modules using lapack_lite
  compile SuperLU using the +i8, link to lapack_lite
     hardly possible, calls to blas use ints

Possible resolution II:
  rewrite lapack_lite_module to use int instead of long (a lot of work)


Other stuff
-----------

benchmarks, to find fastest args parsing for matvec and precon

support additional comment parameter in ll_mat.export_mtx

transpose ll_mat matrix ??

sort column indices in ll_mat.export_mtx (for unsorted list)
